# Age Calculator

## Project Description
This is a simple web-based Age Calculator application. The user inputs their date of birth, and the application calculates and displays their age in years, months, and days.

The project is designed to allow users to calculate their age based on their date of birth. The application restricts the user from selecting a future date to ensure valid input.

## Features
- Input validation to prevent the selection of future dates.
- Calculation of age in years, months, and days.
- Responsive user interface.

## Technologies Used
- HTML
- CSS
- JavaScript

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites
Ensure you have a web browser installed on your computer. This project does not require any additional software.

### Installation
1. Clone the repository to your local machine or download the ZIP file and extract it.

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/age-calculator.git
   ```

2. Open the project folder.
3. Open `index.html` in your preferred web browser.

## Usage
1. Enter your date of birth in the input field. Note that the input field restricts selecting future dates.
2. Click the "Calculate Age" button.
3. Your age in years, months, and days will be displayed below the button.

## Project Structure
```
age-calculator/
├── index.html
├── style.css
└── script.js
```

- `index.html`: The main HTML file that contains the structure of the application.
- `style.css`: The CSS file that handles the styling of the application.
- `script.js`: The JavaScript file that contains the logic for calculating the user's age.

